Gauteng Police have arrested three suspects in Alexandra for drug possession and dealing, as part of a joint intelligence-driven operation. Courtesy #Dstv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng police have arrested three suspects in Alexandra for alleged drug possession and dealing on Sunday. Police spokesperson Brigadier Mathapelo Peters says the suspects will most likely appear before the court on Tuesday. WATCH: Drug bust at Zimbali estate "The suspects are aged between 24 and 47. Each one was arrested in different police operations. We do not believe they are working as a syndicate. Peters adds that the exact type of narcotics, as well as their value, will only be confirmed after forensic officials complete their report. Watch the full interview with Brigadier Mathapelo Peters in the video above.